SkyDexia Plan

Core rule

SkyDex stays the product.
Theia stays the support layer.
No preview-tab behavior is acceptable for SkyDexia launch paths.
If a user clicks SkyDex from the 0s catalog, they must land in the full SkyDex app surface.

Why I previously mentioned non-HTML local targets

Every catalog entry is local to this repo, but not every catalog entry is a single HTML app page.
Some entries resolve to directories, grouped tool buckets, docs, or platform roots.
Those are still local, but they are not all one-file app surfaces.
For actual app pages, the launcher rule is now: open the served app URL, not a Theia preview widget.
For directory-only inventory roots, the fallback is still local filesystem opening until each root gets its own dedicated app shell.

